INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2026-07-10 00:59:11','2026-07-09 16:59:11','<p>A technical data sheet is useful only when the buyer checks whether the material grade, test method, thickness condition, and supplier source match the actual gasket project.</p><h2>Buyer Takeaway</h2><p>Use TDS files for material comparison, then confirm sample performance under the real enclosure design and compression condition.</p>','How to Read a Gasket Material TDS','A technical data sheet helps buyers compare hardness, density, tensile strength, temperature range, and compression properties before selecting a gasket material.','publish','open','open','','how-to-read-gasket-material-tds','','','2026-07-10 03:02:34','2026-07-09 19:02:34','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(2,1,'2026-07-10 00:59:11','2026-07-09 16:59:11','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>这是示范页面。页面和博客文章不同，它的位置是固定的，通常会在站点导航栏显示。很多用户都创建一个「关于」页面，向访客介绍自己。例如：</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>大家好！ 我白天是一名快递小哥，晚上是一名有抱负的魔术师，这是我的网站。 我住在北京，养了一只名叫二哈的小狗。 我平时喜欢喝可乐，还有遛狗。</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>……或这个：</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>XYZ Doohickey 公司成立于 1971 年，自从建立以来，我们一直向社会贡献着优秀 doohickies。我们的公司总部位于天朝魔都，有着超过两千名员工，对魔都政府税收有着巨大贡献。</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>而您，作为一位 WordPress 新用户，我们建议您转到<a href=\"http://localhost:8080/wp-admin/\">您站点的仪表盘</a>，删除本页面，然后创建包含您自己内容的新页面。祝您使用愉快！</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','示例页面','','publish','closed','open','','sample-page','','','2026-07-10 00:59:11','2026-07-09 16:59:11','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0),(3,1,'2026-07-10 00:59:11','2026-07-09 16:59:11','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>This privacy policy explains how SealBridge Supply handles information submitted through website forms, email, and project communication.</p></div>\n<h2>Information We May Collect</h2>\n<ul><li>Name, company, email, phone, and country when you submit an inquiry.</li><li>Project details such as product type, drawing, material, size, quantity, application, and document requirements.</li><li>Website usage information such as pages visited, browser information, and general traffic data if analytics tools are enabled.</li></ul>\n<h2>How We Use Information</h2>\n<p>We use submitted information to understand project requirements, communicate about quotations, coordinate samples or supplier information, improve website content, and maintain business records.</p>\n<h2>Project Drawings and Confidential Information</h2>\n<p>Customer drawings, product photos, and project files are used for quotation and project communication. We do not intentionally publish customer drawings, logos, packaging information, or confidential project files without permission.</p>\n<h2>Sharing With Production Partners</h2>\n<p>When quotation or sampling requires supplier review, relevant project details may be shared with suitable production partners. We aim to share only the information necessary for material, process, quote, and production evaluation.</p>\n<h2>Data Retention</h2>\n<p>Inquiry and project communication records may be retained for business follow-up, customer support, and reference for repeat projects unless deletion is requested and legally or operationally possible.</p>\n<h2>Contact</h2>\n<p>For privacy-related requests, please contact us through the website contact page.</p>','Privacy Policy','','publish','closed','open','','privacy-policy','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=3',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2026-07-10 00:59:24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','自动草稿','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2026-07-10 00:59:24','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?p=4',0,'post','',0),(5,1,'2026-07-10 00:59:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','自动草稿','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2026-07-10 00:59:25','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?p=5',0,'post','',0),(6,1,'2026-07-10 00:59:35','2026-07-09 16:59:35','<!-- wp:page-list /-->','导航栏','','publish','closed','closed','','navigation','','','2026-07-10 00:59:35','2026-07-09 16:59:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?p=6',0,'wp_navigation','',0),(7,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class="material-reference-gallery">
<div class="material-reference-grid">
<figure><img src="/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/materials/material-property-description-01-en.png" alt="English material property description page for NBR HNBR FKM EPDM and silicone" width="1600" height="2200" loading="lazy"><figcaption>Page 1: core sealing elastomers.</figcaption></figure>
<figure><img src="/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/materials/material-property-description-02-en.png" alt="English material property description page for NR SBR IIR CR CSM and FLS" width="1600" height="2200" loading="lazy"><figcaption>Page 2: general-purpose and weathering elastomers.</figcaption></figure>
<figure><img src="/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/materials/material-property-description-03-en.png" alt="English material property description page for FFPM ACM PU GLT FTP and AEM" width="1600" height="2200" loading="lazy"><figcaption>Page 3: specialty and high-performance elastomers.</figcaption></figure>
<figure><img src="/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/materials/material-properties-comparison-04-en.png" alt="English rubber material properties comparison chart and temperature guide" width="1600" height="2200" loading="lazy"><figcaption>Page 4: comparison chart and temperature guide.</figcaption></figure>
</div>
</div>','Materials','','publish','closed','closed','','materials','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=7',0,'page','',0)),(8,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply coordinates suitable process routes for custom rubber, silicone, and foam gasket projects instead of forcing every inquiry into one factory capability.</p></div>\n<h2>Process Routes</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Process</th><th>Suitable Products</th><th>Quotation Details Needed</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Die Cutting</td><td>Flat foam gaskets, adhesive backed gaskets, rubber sheet gaskets</td><td>Drawing, material, thickness, adhesive, tolerance, quantity</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Compression Molding</td><td>Custom rubber gaskets, shaped silicone parts, thicker rubber components</td><td>3D or 2D drawing, material, hardness, tolerance, mold requirement</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Rubber Extrusion</td><td>Cabinet door seals, D-shape strips, U-channel profiles, long sealing strips</td><td>Profile drawing, material, hardness, length, joining requirement</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Adhesive Backing</td><td>Assembly-ready foam and rubber gaskets</td><td>Adhesive brand, surface condition, temperature, peel requirement</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Project Support</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Sample pack coordination</li><li>Drawing review before quotation</li><li>Material and process matching</li><li>Supplier photo and video collection</li><li>Packaging and label detail follow-up</li><li>Document support from production partners</li></ul>','Capabilities','','publish','closed','closed','','capabilities','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=8',0,'page','',0),(9,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Compliance language should be accurate: gasket materials may have supporting documents, while final enclosure sealing performance depends on material, design, compression, assembly, and testing.</p></div>\n<h2>Supplier Document Workflow</h2>\n<p>For projects that require certificates or material documents, we first confirm the exact material, supplier, production process, and customer requirement. Then we coordinate available documents from suitable production partners and review whether the document scope matches the selected material or project.</p>\n<h2>Documents We Help Coordinate</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>RoHS material reports</li><li>REACH declarations or reports</li><li>UL94 material grade information when available</li><li>TDS and SDS documents</li><li>Material data such as hardness, density, and temperature range</li><li>Supplier capability and production photos</li></ul>\n<h2>Certificate Review Points</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Document</th><th>What We Check</th><th>Important Note</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>RoHS</td><td>Material name, test item, test date, supplier or material source</td><td>RoHS is material-related and should not be treated as a universal factory certificate.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>REACH</td><td>Declaration or test scope, SVHC reference, document date</td><td>Customer requirement should be confirmed because REACH scope may change over time.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>UL94</td><td>Material grade, thickness condition, supplier statement or data sheet</td><td>UL94 grade belongs to tested material conditions, not automatically every finished gasket.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>TDS</td><td>Hardness, density, tensile strength, temperature range, compression set</td><td>TDS is useful for engineering review but must match selected material.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>SDS</td><td>Material safety handling information and supplier source</td><td>SDS is not a performance certificate; it supports safety and handling review.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>ISO 9001</td><td>Factory quality management certificate if available</td><td>Factory system certificates should be checked for company name, validity, and scope.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>IP Rating Notes</h2>\n<p>A gasket alone should not be described as IP65 or IP66 certified. IP-rated sealing belongs to the final enclosure assembly and test condition. We can help choose materials and processes commonly used for IP-rated enclosure sealing support.</p>\n<h2>Preferred Compliance Wording</h2>\n<p>SealBridge Supply helps coordinate material documents and compliance information such as RoHS, REACH, UL94 material grade information, TDS, and SDS when available from production partners. Final suitability should be confirmed based on the selected material, supplier document, and project application.</p>','Quality &amp; Compliance','','trash','closed','closed','','quality-compliance__trashed','','','2026-07-10 07:15:04','2026-07-09 23:15:04','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=9',0,'page','',0),(10,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply is a sourcing and project coordination partner focused on custom gaskets for electrical enclosures, control cabinets, and outdoor equipment.</p></div>\n<h2>Company Background</h2>\n<p>SealBridge Supply was created for overseas B2B buyers who need custom rubber, silicone, and foam gasket support but do not want to spend weeks sorting out materials, processes, supplier communication, samples, and compliance documents. The brand focuses on electrical enclosure, control cabinet, junction box, EV charger cabinet, solar inverter enclosure, LED lighting housing, telecom cabinet, and HVAC equipment sealing projects.</p>\n<p>We position ourselves as a custom gasket sourcing and project coordination partner. That means we do not present every product as if it comes from one single factory. Instead, we help customers clarify the project requirement, match the suitable process route, coordinate samples and supplier information, and organize quotation details before production follow-up.</p>\n<h2>What We Coordinate</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Material comparison for EPDM, silicone, NBR, CR, EVA, PU foam, and other gasket materials</li><li>Process matching for die cutting, compression molding, rubber extrusion, adhesive backing, and custom sampling</li><li>Supplier communication, sample photos, product videos, packaging details, and quote parameters</li><li>Document support such as TDS, SDS, RoHS, REACH, and UL94 material information when available</li></ul>\n<h2>Supplier Network</h2>\n<p>We maintain a working network of 20+ screened production partners and factory contacts across rubber, silicone, foam, adhesive-backed die cutting, molding, and extrusion directions. The number is used as a practical sourcing range rather than a claim that every project will use every factory. For each inquiry, we select partners based on product fit, process route, sample response, document support, and communication quality.</p>\n<h2>Who We Serve</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Electrical enclosure manufacturers</li><li>Control cabinet manufacturers</li><li>Junction box manufacturers</li><li>EV charger cabinet manufacturers</li><li>Solar inverter enclosure manufacturers</li><li>LED lighting housing manufacturers</li></ul>\n<h2>How We Work</h2>\n<p>Our work starts from application and drawing review, not from a generic price list. A useful gasket quote usually needs the drawing, material target, thickness or profile size, hardness or density, adhesive requirement, quantity, application environment, and document requirements. We help organize those details so the supplier conversation is faster and more accurate.</p>','About','','publish','closed','closed','','about','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=10',0,'page','',0),(11,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Send the drawing, material, size, quantity, application, and certificate requirements. Clear project details help reduce back-and-forth and improve quotation accuracy.</p></div>\n<h2>Quote Information Checklist</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Drawing or photo</li><li>Material target</li><li>Thickness or profile size</li><li>Hardness or density</li><li>Adhesive backing requirement</li><li>Order quantity and sample quantity</li><li>Application environment</li><li>RoHS, REACH, UL94, TDS, or SDS needs</li></ul>\n<h2>Request Form Mockup</h2>\n<label>Name</label><label>Email</label><label>WhatsApp</label><label>Product TypeElectrical Enclosure GasketControl Cabinet Sealing StripEPDM Foam GasketSilicone GasketAdhesive Backed Die Cut GasketCustom Rubber Gasket</label><label>Project Details<textarea name=\"message\"></textarea></label><button class=\"button\" type=\"button\">Prepare Quote Details</button>\n<h2>Fast Contact Channels</h2>\n<div class=\"contact-channel-grid\"><a href=\"https://wa.me/8618770214461\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>WhatsApp</strong><span>+86 187 7021 4461</span></a></div>','Contact / Request a Quote','','publish','closed','closed','','contact','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?page_id=11',0,'page','',0),(12,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Flat, foam, or molded gaskets for electrical enclosures, junction boxes, outdoor covers, and equipment housings.</p></div><h2>Product Positioning</h2><p>Use this category when the buyer needs a gasket for an electrical box, enclosure cover, access panel, outdoor housing, or IP-rating support project. Confirm drawing, gasket path, thickness, compression target, material, quantity, and document needs.</p><h2>Electrical Enclosure Gasket Applications</h2><p>Electrical enclosure gaskets are used around enclosure covers, access doors, junction boxes, outdoor electrical boxes, equipment housings, and control panels where dust and water sealing support is required. Common project goals include stable compression, outdoor aging resistance, cleaner installation, and material documents for export customers.</p><h2>Common Material Direction</h2><p>EPDM foam is often selected for outdoor electrical enclosure gasket projects because it supports weather, ozone, aging, and water resistance. Silicone foam or silicone rubber may be considered when the enclosure faces wider temperature exposure, softer sealing requirements, or LED/electronics-related heat conditions.</p><h2>Quote Details for Enclosure Gaskets</h2><p>For a useful quote, send the enclosure drawing, gasket path, cover size, thickness, compression target, material preference, adhesive requirement, order quantity, and document needs such as RoHS, REACH, UL94 material information, TDS, or SDS.</p><h2>Common Quote Parameters</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Drawing or sample photo</li><li>Material and color</li><li>Thickness, size, or profile drawing</li><li>Hardness or density</li><li>Adhesive requirement</li><li>Quantity and compliance documents</li></ul>','Electrical Enclosure Gaskets','Flat, foam, or molded gaskets for electrical enclosures, junction boxes, outdoor covers, and equipment housings.','publish','closed','closed','','electrical-enclosure-gaskets','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?product=electrical-enclosure-gaskets',0,'product','',0),(13,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Extruded or foam sealing strips for control cabinets, distribution cabinets, server cabinets, and cabinet door edges.</p></div><h2>Product Positioning</h2><p>Use this category for cabinet door seals, edge seals, and long strip profiles. Confirm profile drawing, door gap, material, hardness or density, length, corner treatment, and installation method.</p><h2>Control Cabinet Door Seal Applications</h2><p>Control cabinet sealing strips are used for cabinet doors, distribution cabinets, electrical cabinets, server cabinets, telecom cabinets, and industrial panels. These parts help close door gaps, reduce dust ingress, protect edges, and maintain repeatable compression after frequent cabinet access.</p><h2>Profile and Material Options</h2><p>Typical cabinet door seal profiles include bulb seals, D-shape strips, U-channel edge seals, self-grip profiles, and custom extruded rubber profiles. EPDM rubber is a common starting point for general cabinet sealing, while silicone rubber may be selected for softer sealing or broader temperature conditions.</p><h2>Quote Details for Cabinet Seals</h2><p>Useful inputs include a profile drawing, sample photo, cabinet door gap, installation method, material, hardness or sponge density, color, roll length or cut length, corner joining requirement, packing method, and annual quantity.</p><h2>Common Quote Parameters</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Drawing or sample photo</li><li>Material and color</li><li>Thickness, size, or profile drawing</li><li>Hardness or density</li><li>Adhesive requirement</li><li>Quantity and compliance documents</li></ul>','Control Cabinet Sealing Strips','Extruded or foam sealing strips for control cabinets, distribution cabinets, server cabinets, and cabinet door edges.','publish','closed','closed','','control-cabinet-sealing-strips','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?product=control-cabinet-sealing-strips',0,'product','',0),(14,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Closed-cell EPDM sponge and foam gaskets for outdoor waterproof, dustproof, weather-resistant sealing.</p></div><h2>Product Positioning</h2><p>Use this category when the project needs outdoor aging resistance, compression recovery, water resistance support, or foam sealing around covers and panels. Confirm density, thickness, adhesive requirement, and compression gap.</p><h2>EPDM Foam Gasket Applications</h2><p>EPDM foam gaskets and EPDM sponge gaskets are used for outdoor waterproof and dustproof sealing around enclosure doors, access panels, junction boxes, solar inverter enclosures, EV charger cabinets, battery cabinets, HVAC equipment, and other weather-exposed housings.</p><h2>Closed-cell Foam Selection</h2><p>Closed-cell EPDM foam is often preferred when the project needs compression recovery, low water absorption, weather resistance, and adhesive-backed assembly. Thickness, density, compression force, adhesive type, and liner format should be confirmed before sampling.</p><h2>Quote Details for EPDM Foam Gaskets</h2><p>Send the drawing or dimensions, target thickness, density or compression requirement, adhesive need, working temperature, outdoor exposure condition, quantity, and whether the part should be supplied as strips, die-cut frames, kiss-cut sheets, or roll material.</p><h2>Common Quote Parameters</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Drawing or sample photo</li><li>Material and color</li><li>Thickness, size, or profile drawing</li><li>Hardness or density</li><li>Adhesive requirement</li><li>Quantity and compliance documents</li></ul>','EPDM Foam Gaskets','Closed-cell EPDM sponge and foam gaskets for outdoor waterproof, dustproof, weather-resistant sealing.','publish','closed','closed','','epdm-foam-gaskets','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?product=epdm-foam-gaskets',0,'product','',0),(15,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Silicone rubber and silicone foam gaskets for high/low temperature, outdoor electronics, LED housings, and equipment covers.</p></div><h2>Product Positioning</h2><p>Use this category when softness, UV exposure, temperature range, or silicone material is important. Confirm solid or foam silicone, hardness, color, temperature range, food/flame requirements, and adhesive surface treatment.</p><h2>Silicone Gasket Applications</h2><p>Silicone gaskets and silicone rubber gaskets are commonly used for LED lighting housings, outdoor electronics, equipment covers, battery enclosures, high-temperature covers, and projects where softness, UV exposure, or temperature range is more important than lowest material cost.</p><h2>Solid Silicone and Silicone Foam</h2><p>Solid silicone can be used for molded or die-cut gasket parts where stable elasticity and temperature resistance are required. Silicone foam can be useful for softer compression sealing around covers, lenses, and electronic housings. Color, hardness, surface finish, adhesive treatment, and flame or food-grade requirements should be confirmed.</p><h2>Quote Details for Silicone Gaskets</h2><p>For quotation, provide a 2D or 3D drawing, solid or foam silicone preference, hardness, color, temperature exposure, UV condition, adhesive requirement, tolerance, quantity, and any compliance documents requested by the buyer.</p><h2>Common Quote Parameters</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Drawing or sample photo</li><li>Material and color</li><li>Thickness, size, or profile drawing</li><li>Hardness or density</li><li>Adhesive requirement</li><li>Quantity and compliance documents</li></ul>','Silicone Gaskets','Silicone rubber and silicone foam gaskets for high/low temperature, outdoor electronics, LED housings, and equipment covers.','publish','closed','closed','','silicone-gaskets','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?product=silicone-gaskets',0,'product','',0),(16,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Die-cut foam or rubber gaskets with adhesive backing for quick peel-and-stick assembly on boxes, covers, and panels.</p></div><h2>Product Positioning</h2><p>Use this category when the buyer wants release-liner-backed parts for faster assembly. Confirm material, thickness, adhesive brand or grade, liner type, tolerance, packing format, and surface condition.</p><h2>Adhesive Backed Die Cut Gasket Applications</h2><p>Adhesive backed die cut gaskets, self-adhesive gaskets, and peel-and-stick foam gaskets are used when assembly speed and clean placement matter. They are common for junction boxes, access covers, electronic housings, enclosure panels, LED housings, and small gasket parts that need release liner support.</p><h2>Die Cutting and Adhesive Options</h2><p>Common material options include EPDM foam, EVA foam, PE foam, silicone foam, rubber sheet, and adhesive-backed gasket materials. The adhesive brand or grade, release liner, surface condition, tolerance, and packing format affect both production and assembly performance.</p><h2>Quote Details for Die Cut Gaskets</h2><p>Useful files include DXF, PDF, or CAD drawings, material and thickness target, adhesive requirement, liner type, tolerance, assembly surface, sheet or roll packing preference, sample quantity, and bulk quantity.</p><h2>Common Quote Parameters</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Drawing or sample photo</li><li>Material and color</li><li>Thickness, size, or profile drawing</li><li>Hardness or density</li><li>Adhesive requirement</li><li>Quantity and compliance documents</li></ul>','Adhesive Backed Die Cut Gaskets','Die-cut foam or rubber gaskets with adhesive backing for quick peel-and-stick assembly on boxes, covers, and panels.','publish','closed','closed','','adhesive-backed-die-cut-gaskets','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?product=adhesive-backed-die-cut-gaskets',0,'product','',0),(17,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Drawing-based custom rubber gaskets and seals for non-standard sizes, samples, molded parts, and custom projects.</p></div><h2>Product Positioning</h2><p>Use this category for customer drawings, samples, custom dimensions, molded gaskets, cut gaskets, or special rubber seals. Confirm material, hardness, tolerance, tooling, sample plan, bulk quantity, and compliance documents.</p><h2>Custom Rubber Gasket Applications</h2><p>Custom rubber gaskets and custom rubber seals according to drawing are used when standard gasket sizes or profiles cannot match the project. They may be molded, die-cut, extruded, bonded, or assembled based on the drawing, sample, material, tolerance, and quantity.</p><h2>Drawing-based Rubber Seal Options</h2><p>Common materials include EPDM, NBR, silicone, neoprene / CR, and custom compounds. EPDM is often used for outdoor sealing, NBR for oil-resistant applications, silicone for temperature-sensitive sealing, and CR for balanced industrial performance. Tooling may be required for molded or special-profile parts.</p><h2>Quote Details for Custom Rubber Gaskets</h2><p>Send the drawing or physical sample, material target, hardness, dimensions, tolerance, surface finish, application environment, sample plan, bulk quantity, inspection criteria, packaging requirement, and document needs.</p><h2>Common Quote Parameters</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Drawing or sample photo</li><li>Material and color</li><li>Thickness, size, or profile drawing</li><li>Hardness or density</li><li>Adhesive requirement</li><li>Quantity and compliance documents</li></ul>','Custom Rubber Gaskets','Drawing-based custom rubber gaskets and seals for non-standard sizes, samples, molded parts, and custom projects.','publish','closed','closed','','custom-rubber-gaskets','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?product=custom-rubber-gaskets',0,'product','',0),(18,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Gasket selection guide for outdoor electrical boxes, equipment enclosures, and weather-exposed cabinet assemblies.</p></div><h2>Typical Gasket Requirements</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Outdoor aging resistance</li><li>Compression recovery</li><li>Dust and water sealing support</li><li>Suitable adhesive or mechanical installation</li><li>Stable supply and sampling</li><li>Material documents when available</li></ul>','Outdoor Electrical Enclosures','Gasket selection guide for outdoor electrical boxes, equipment enclosures, and weather-exposed cabinet assemblies.','publish','closed','closed','','outdoor-electrical-enclosures','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?application=outdoor-electrical-enclosures',0,'application','',0),(19,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Sealing strip and gasket guide for industrial control cabinet doors, edges, and repeated access panels.</p></div><h2>Typical Gasket Requirements</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Outdoor aging resistance</li><li>Compression recovery</li><li>Dust and water sealing support</li><li>Suitable adhesive or mechanical installation</li><li>Stable supply and sampling</li><li>Material documents when available</li></ul>','Control Cabinets','Sealing strip and gasket guide for industrial control cabinet doors, edges, and repeated access panels.','publish','closed','closed','','control-cabinets','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?application=control-cabinets',0,'application','',0),(20,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Compact gasket and adhesive-backed sealing guide for junction box covers and small enclosure assemblies.</p></div><h2>Typical Gasket Requirements</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Outdoor aging resistance</li><li>Compression recovery</li><li>Dust and water sealing support</li><li>Suitable adhesive or mechanical installation</li><li>Stable supply and sampling</li><li>Material documents when available</li></ul>','Junction Boxes','Compact gasket and adhesive-backed sealing guide for junction box covers and small enclosure assemblies.','publish','closed','closed','','junction-boxes','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?application=junction-boxes',0,'application','',0),(21,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Outdoor gasket selection guide for EV charger cabinet doors, access panels, and electrical modules.</p></div><h2>Typical Gasket Requirements</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Outdoor aging resistance</li><li>Compression recovery</li><li>Dust and water sealing support</li><li>Suitable adhesive or mechanical installation</li><li>Stable supply and sampling</li><li>Material documents when available</li></ul>','EV Charger Cabinets','Outdoor gasket selection guide for EV charger cabinet doors, access panels, and electrical modules.','publish','closed','closed','','ev-charger-cabinets','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?application=ev-charger-cabinets',0,'application','',0),(22,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>EPDM and silicone gasket guide for solar inverter enclosures exposed to UV, heat, and outdoor humidity.</p></div><h2>Typical Gasket Requirements</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Outdoor aging resistance</li><li>Compression recovery</li><li>Dust and water sealing support</li><li>Suitable adhesive or mechanical installation</li><li>Stable supply and sampling</li><li>Material documents when available</li></ul>','Solar Inverter Enclosures','EPDM and silicone gasket guide for solar inverter enclosures exposed to UV, heat, and outdoor humidity.','publish','closed','closed','','solar-inverter-enclosures','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?application=solar-inverter-enclosures',0,'application','',0),(23,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Silicone and foam gasket guide for LED lighting covers, lenses, housings, and outdoor fixtures.</p></div><h2>Typical Gasket Requirements</h2><ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Outdoor aging resistance</li><li>Compression recovery</li><li>Dust and water sealing support</li><li>Suitable adhesive or mechanical installation</li><li>Stable supply and sampling</li><li>Material documents when available</li></ul>','LED Lighting Housings','Silicone and foam gasket guide for LED lighting covers, lenses, housings, and outdoor fixtures.','publish','closed','closed','','led-lighting-housings','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?application=led-lighting-housings',0,'application','',0),(24,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<p>EPDM is often a practical outdoor enclosure material because it offers strong weather, ozone, aging, and water resistance. Silicone is useful when broader temperature range, softness, or UV stability is more important. The better choice depends on compression, cost, exposure, and document requirements.</p><h2>Buyer Takeaway</h2><p>Confirm the actual application, material data, assembly method, and document requirements before locking the specification.</p>','EPDM vs Silicone for Outdoor Enclosure Gaskets','EPDM is often a practica&hellip;','publish','open','open','','epdm-vs-silicone-outdoor-enclosure-gaskets','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?p=24',0,'post','',0),(25,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<p>A useful quote request should include drawing, material, thickness, adhesive requirement, tolerance, quantity, application, and compliance needs. Clear inputs help suppliers avoid assumptions and reduce quotation cycles.</p><h2>Buyer Takeaway</h2><p>Confirm the actual application, material data, assembly method, and document requirements before locking the specification.</p>','What Information Is Needed for a Custom Die Cut Gasket Quote?','A useful quote request s&hellip;','publish','open','open','','custom-die-cut-gasket-quote-information','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?p=25',0,'post','',0),(26,1,'2026-07-10 01:07:22','2026-07-09 17:07:22','<p>A gasket alone should not usually be described as IP65 or IP66 certified. The IP rating belongs to the final enclosure assembly under test conditions. Gasket material and compression design can support that target, but the enclosure must be verified as a system.</p><h2>Buyer Takeaway</h2><p>Confirm the actual application, material data, assembly method, and document requirements before locking the specification.</p>','Can a Gasket Be IP65 or IP66 Certified?','A gasket alone should no&hellip;','publish','open','open','','can-a-gasket-be-ip65-or-ip66-certified','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/?p=26',0,'post','',0),(35,0,'2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Material choice decides compression recovery, outdoor life, adhesive performance, cost, and the documents that can be provided for a project.</p></div>\n<h2>Material Options</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Material</th><th>Best Fit</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>EPDM</td><td>Outdoor electrical enclosures, control cabinets, HVAC units</td><td>Good weather, ozone, aging, and water resistance. Not ideal for long oil exposure.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Silicone</td><td>High or low temperature, UV exposure, soft sealing</td><td>Flexible and stable, usually higher cost than EPDM or NBR.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>NBR</td><td>Oil-resistant gasket applications</td><td>Useful around oils and fuels, less preferred for long outdoor exposure.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Neoprene / CR</td><td>Balanced industrial sealing and foam gaskets</td><td>Good general-purpose option when weather, oil, and flame behavior all matter.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>EVA / PU Foam</td><td>Cushioning, dust sealing, packaging, low-pressure sealing</td><td>Confirm water absorption, aging, and compression set before outdoor use.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>How We Compare Materials</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Outdoor exposure and UV aging</li><li>Compression set and recovery</li><li>Thickness, density, and hardness</li><li>Adhesive backing compatibility</li><li>RoHS, REACH, TDS, and SDS availability</li><li>Cost target and production process</li></ul>','Materials','','inherit','closed','closed','','7-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','',7,'http://localhost:8080/?p=35',0,'revision','',0),(36,0,'2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply coordinates suitable process routes for custom rubber, silicone, and foam gasket projects instead of forcing every inquiry into one factory capability.</p></div>\n<h2>Process Routes</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Process</th><th>Suitable Products</th><th>Quotation Details Needed</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Die Cutting</td><td>Flat foam gaskets, adhesive backed gaskets, rubber sheet gaskets</td><td>Drawing, material, thickness, adhesive, tolerance, quantity</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Compression Molding</td><td>Custom rubber gaskets, shaped silicone parts, thicker rubber components</td><td>3D or 2D drawing, material, hardness, tolerance, mold requirement</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Rubber Extrusion</td><td>Cabinet door seals, D-shape strips, U-channel profiles, long sealing strips</td><td>Profile drawing, material, hardness, length, joining requirement</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Adhesive Backing</td><td>Assembly-ready foam and rubber gaskets</td><td>Adhesive brand, surface condition, temperature, peel requirement</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Project Support</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Sample pack coordination</li><li>Drawing review before quotation</li><li>Material and process matching</li><li>Supplier photo and video collection</li><li>Packaging and label detail follow-up</li><li>Document support from production partners</li></ul>','Capabilities','','inherit','closed','closed','','8-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','',8,'http://localhost:8080/?p=36',0,'revision','',0),(37,0,'2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Compliance language should be accurate: gasket materials may have supporting documents, while final enclosure sealing performance depends on material, design, compression, assembly, and testing.</p></div>\n<h2>Documents We Help Coordinate</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>RoHS material reports</li><li>REACH declarations or reports</li><li>UL94 material grade information when available</li><li>TDS and SDS documents</li><li>Material data such as hardness, density, and temperature range</li><li>Supplier capability and production photos</li></ul>\n<h2>IP Rating Notes</h2>\n<p>A gasket alone should not be described as IP65 or IP66 certified. IP-rated sealing belongs to the final enclosure assembly and test condition. We can help choose materials and processes commonly used for IP-rated enclosure sealing support.</p>\n<h2>Preferred Compliance Wording</h2>\n<p>SealBridge Supply helps coordinate material documents and compliance information such as RoHS, REACH, UL94 material grade information, TDS, and SDS when available from production partners. Final suitability should be confirmed based on the selected material, supplier document, and project application.</p>','Quality &amp; Compliance','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','',9,'http://localhost:8080/?p=37',0,'revision','',0),(38,0,'2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply is a sourcing and project coordination partner focused on custom gaskets for electrical enclosures, control cabinets, and outdoor equipment.</p></div>\n<h2>What We Do</h2>\n<p>We help overseas B2B buyers match rubber, silicone, and foam gasket requirements with suitable production partners. The goal is clear communication, practical sampling, organized quotation details, and reliable follow-up.</p>\n<h2>Who We Serve</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Electrical enclosure manufacturers</li><li>Control cabinet manufacturers</li><li>Junction box manufacturers</li><li>EV charger cabinet manufacturers</li><li>Solar inverter enclosure manufacturers</li><li>LED lighting housing manufacturers</li></ul>\n<h2>Positioning</h2>\n<p>We are not presenting as a single factory. We operate as a focused custom gasket sourcing and coordination partner for projects that need material, process, sample, and document alignment.</p>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','',10,'http://localhost:8080/?p=38',0,'revision','',0),(39,0,'2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Send the drawing, material, size, quantity, application, and certificate requirements. Clear project details help reduce back-and-forth and improve quotation accuracy.</p></div>\n<h2>Quote Information Checklist</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Drawing or photo</li><li>Material target</li><li>Thickness or profile size</li><li>Hardness or density</li><li>Adhesive backing requirement</li><li>Order quantity and sample quantity</li><li>Application environment</li><li>RoHS, REACH, UL94, TDS, or SDS needs</li></ul>\n<h2>Request Form Mockup</h2>\n<label>Name</label><label>Email</label><label>Product TypeElectrical Enclosure GasketControl Cabinet Sealing StripEPDM Foam GasketSilicone GasketAdhesive Backed Die Cut GasketCustom Rubber Gasket</label><label>Project Details<textarea name=\"message\"></textarea></label><button class=\"button\" type=\"button\">Prepare Quote Details</button>','Contact / Request a Quote','','inherit','closed','closed','','11-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','',11,'http://localhost:8080/?p=39',0,'revision','',0),(40,0,'2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','<p>EPDM is often a practical outdoor enclosure material because it offers strong weather, ozone, aging, and water resistance. Silicone is useful when broader temperature range, softness, or UV stability is more important. The better choice depends on compression, cost, exposure, and document requirements.</p><h2>Buyer Takeaway</h2><p>Confirm the actual application, material data, assembly method, and document requirements before locking the specification.</p>','EPDM vs Silicone for Outdoor Enclosure Gaskets','EPDM is often a practica&hellip;','inherit','closed','closed','','24-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','',24,'http://localhost:8080/?p=40',0,'revision','',0),(41,0,'2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','<p>A useful quote request should include drawing, material, thickness, adhesive requirement, tolerance, quantity, application, and compliance needs. Clear inputs help suppliers avoid assumptions and reduce quotation cycles.</p><h2>Buyer Takeaway</h2><p>Confirm the actual application, material data, assembly method, and document requirements before locking the specification.</p>','What Information Is Needed for a Custom Die Cut Gasket Quote?','A useful quote request s&hellip;','inherit','closed','closed','','25-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','',25,'http://localhost:8080/?p=41',0,'revision','',0),(42,0,'2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','<p>A gasket alone should not usually be described as IP65 or IP66 certified. The IP rating belongs to the final enclosure assembly under test conditions. Gasket material and compression design can support that target, but the enclosure must be verified as a system.</p><h2>Buyer Takeaway</h2><p>Confirm the actual application, material data, assembly method, and document requirements before locking the specification.</p>','Can a Gasket Be IP65 or IP66 Certified?','A gasket alone should no&hellip;','inherit','closed','closed','','26-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:08:15','2026-07-09 17:08:15','',26,'http://localhost:8080/?p=42',0,'revision','',0),(74,0,'2026-07-10 01:44:06','2026-07-09 17:44:06','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply is a sourcing and project coordination partner focused on custom gaskets for electrical enclosures, control cabinets, and outdoor equipment.</p></div>\n<h2>Company Background</h2>\n<p>SealBridge Supply was created for overseas B2B buyers who need custom rubber, silicone, and foam gasket support but do not want to spend weeks sorting out materials, processes, supplier communication, samples, and compliance documents. The brand focuses on electrical enclosure, control cabinet, junction box, EV charger cabinet, solar inverter enclosure, LED lighting housing, telecom cabinet, and HVAC equipment sealing projects.</p>\n<p>We position ourselves as a custom gasket sourcing and project coordination partner. That means we do not present every product as if it comes from one single factory. Instead, we help customers clarify the project requirement, match the suitable process route, coordinate samples and supplier information, and organize quotation details before production follow-up.</p>\n<h2>What We Coordinate</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Material comparison for EPDM, silicone, NBR, CR, EVA, PU foam, and other gasket materials</li><li>Process matching for die cutting, compression molding, rubber extrusion, adhesive backing, and custom sampling</li><li>Supplier communication, sample photos, product videos, packaging details, and quote parameters</li><li>Document support such as TDS, SDS, RoHS, REACH, and UL94 material information when available</li></ul>\n<h2>Who We Serve</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Electrical enclosure manufacturers</li><li>Control cabinet manufacturers</li><li>Junction box manufacturers</li><li>EV charger cabinet manufacturers</li><li>Solar inverter enclosure manufacturers</li><li>LED lighting housing manufacturers</li></ul>\n<h2>How We Work</h2>\n<p>Our work starts from application and drawing review, not from a generic price list. A useful gasket quote usually needs the drawing, material target, thickness or profile size, hardness or density, adhesive requirement, quantity, application environment, and document requirements. We help organize those details so the supplier conversation is faster and more accurate.</p>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:44:06','2026-07-09 17:44:06','',10,'http://localhost:8080/?p=74',0,'revision','',0),(75,1,'2026-07-10 01:44:06','2026-07-09 17:44:06','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>A clear sourcing process reduces back-and-forth, avoids wrong material assumptions, and helps customers get more useful gasket quotations.</p></div>\n<h2>Step 1: Application Review</h2>\n<p>We first confirm where the gasket will be used: outdoor electrical enclosure, control cabinet, junction box, EV charger cabinet, solar inverter enclosure, LED lighting housing, or another equipment assembly.</p>\n<h2>Step 2: Drawing and Parameter Check</h2>\n<table><tbody><tr><th>Drawing</th><td>2D drawing, 3D file, profile drawing, sample photo, or gasket path sketch.</td></tr><tr><th>Material</th><td>EPDM, silicone, NBR, CR, EVA, PU foam, or open material recommendation.</td></tr><tr><th>Dimensions</th><td>Thickness, width, profile size, tolerance, length, and compression gap.</td></tr><tr><th>Assembly</th><td>Adhesive backing, screw compression, groove installation, edge trim, or custom fixture.</td></tr><tr><th>Documents</th><td>RoHS, REACH, UL94 material information, TDS, SDS, or other buyer requirements.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h2>Step 3: Material and Process Matching</h2>\n<p>We compare whether the project is better suited for die cutting, compression molding, rubber extrusion, adhesive lamination, or custom sampling. The goal is to match the project to the right production route before asking for price.</p>\n<h2>Step 4: Supplier Coordination and Quotation</h2>\n<p>We organize the quote request, coordinate supplier questions, collect sample photos or videos where available, and help clarify mold cost, lead time, MOQ, packaging, and document support.</p>\n<h2>Step 5: Sampling and Production Follow-up</h2>\n<p>For suitable projects, we coordinate sample preparation, sample labels, packaging information, and production follow-up details so the customer can review the part before bulk order decisions.</p>','Sourcing Process','','publish','closed','closed','','sourcing-process','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/sourcing-process/',0,'page','',0),(76,1,'2026-07-10 01:44:06','2026-07-09 17:44:06','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Common questions from buyers sourcing custom enclosure gaskets, sealing strips, foam gaskets, and adhesive-backed die cut parts.</p></div>\n<h2>Can you provide a price without a drawing?</h2>\n<p>A rough range may be possible for standard materials, but accurate quotation usually needs drawing, size, material, thickness or profile details, quantity, and application information.</p>\n<h2>Can a gasket itself be IP65 or IP66 certified?</h2>\n<p>Usually no. IP rating belongs to the final enclosure assembly and test condition. The gasket can support IP-rated sealing, but the complete box, door, compression design, and installation must be tested as a system.</p>\n<h2>Do you support small-batch samples?</h2>\n<p>Sample support depends on material, process, tooling, supplier schedule, and order potential. Die-cut samples are often easier than molded or extruded custom profiles that require tooling.</p>\n<h2>What documents can be provided?</h2>\n<p>Depending on the material and supplier, available documents may include TDS, SDS, RoHS, REACH, and UL94 material grade information. Document availability should be confirmed for the selected material and production partner.</p>\n<h2>Which material is best for outdoor enclosures?</h2>\n<p>EPDM foam is often a practical starting point for outdoor enclosure sealing because of weather, ozone, aging, and water resistance. Silicone may be better for broader temperature range or softer sealing requirements.</p>\n<h2>Do you sell standard products or custom parts?</h2>\n<p>The site focuses on custom gasket sourcing. Some standard samples and common profiles may be available, but most useful quotations are based on the customer drawing, material, quantity, and application.</p>','FAQ','','publish','closed','closed','','faq','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/faq/',0,'page','',0),(77,0,'2026-07-10 01:44:06','2026-07-09 17:44:06','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>This privacy policy explains how SealBridge Supply handles information submitted through website forms, email, and project communication.</p></div>\n<h2>Information We May Collect</h2>\n<ul><li>Name, company, email, phone, and country when you submit an inquiry.</li><li>Project details such as product type, drawing, material, size, quantity, application, and document requirements.</li><li>Website usage information such as pages visited, browser information, and general traffic data if analytics tools are enabled.</li></ul>\n<h2>How We Use Information</h2>\n<p>We use submitted information to understand project requirements, communicate about quotations, coordinate samples or supplier information, improve website content, and maintain business records.</p>\n<h2>Project Drawings and Confidential Information</h2>\n<p>Customer drawings, product photos, and project files are used for quotation and project communication. We do not intentionally publish customer drawings, logos, packaging information, or confidential project files without permission.</p>\n<h2>Sharing With Production Partners</h2>\n<p>When quotation or sampling requires supplier review, relevant project details may be shared with suitable production partners. We aim to share only the information necessary for material, process, quote, and production evaluation.</p>\n<h2>Data Retention</h2>\n<p>Inquiry and project communication records may be retained for business follow-up, customer support, and reference for repeat projects unless deletion is requested and legally or operationally possible.</p>\n<h2>Contact</h2>\n<p>For privacy-related requests, please contact us through the website contact page.</p>','Privacy Policy','','inherit','closed','closed','','3-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:44:06','2026-07-09 17:44:06','',3,'http://localhost:8080/?p=77',0,'revision','',0),(78,1,'2026-07-10 01:44:06','2026-07-09 17:44:06','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>These terms describe the general use of the SealBridge Supply website and project communication. They are written for B2B sourcing and quotation discussions.</p></div>\n<h2>Website Information</h2>\n<p>Website content is provided for general product, material, process, and sourcing reference. It should not be treated as a final engineering specification without project-specific confirmation.</p>\n<h2>Quotation and Availability</h2>\n<p>Prices, lead times, MOQ, tooling cost, sample cost, document availability, and production capacity depend on material, drawing, quantity, supplier review, and current production conditions. Formal quotations should be confirmed in writing for each project.</p>\n<h2>Samples and Product Suitability</h2>\n<p>Samples are used for evaluation and confirmation. Final product suitability should be reviewed by the buyer based on the actual application, assembly design, environmental condition, and required testing.</p>\n<h2>Compliance and IP Rating</h2>\n<p>Material documents such as RoHS, REACH, UL94 information, TDS, and SDS may be coordinated when available. IP ratings apply to complete enclosure assemblies and test conditions, not to a gasket alone.</p>\n<h2>Customer Files</h2>\n<p>Customers are responsible for ensuring that drawings, photos, logos, and technical files submitted for quotation can be shared for project evaluation. We aim to use those files only for sourcing, quotation, sampling, and production communication.</p>\n<h2>Limitation</h2>\n<p>SealBridge Supply is a sourcing and coordination brand. Final purchase terms, inspection criteria, packaging, shipping, and compliance obligations should be confirmed in written project documents.</p>','Terms of Service','','publish','closed','closed','','terms-of-service','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/terms-of-service/',0,'page','',0),(87,0,'2026-07-10 01:48:15','2026-07-09 17:48:15','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Compliance language should be accurate: gasket materials may have supporting documents, while final enclosure sealing performance depends on material, design, compression, assembly, and testing.</p></div>\n<h2>Supplier Document Workflow</h2>\n<p>For projects that require certificates or material documents, we first confirm the exact material, supplier, production process, and customer requirement. Then we coordinate available documents from suitable production partners and review whether the document scope matches the selected material or project.</p>\n<h2>Documents We Help Coordinate</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>RoHS material reports</li><li>REACH declarations or reports</li><li>UL94 material grade information when available</li><li>TDS and SDS documents</li><li>Material data such as hardness, density, and temperature range</li><li>Supplier capability and production photos</li></ul>\n<h2>Certificate Review Points</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Document</th><th>What We Check</th><th>Important Note</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>RoHS</td><td>Material name, test item, test date, supplier or material source</td><td>RoHS is material-related and should not be treated as a universal factory certificate.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>REACH</td><td>Declaration or test scope, SVHC reference, document date</td><td>Customer requirement should be confirmed because REACH scope may change over time.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>UL94</td><td>Material grade, thickness condition, supplier statement or data sheet</td><td>UL94 grade belongs to tested material conditions, not automatically every finished gasket.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>TDS</td><td>Hardness, density, tensile strength, temperature range, compression set</td><td>TDS is useful for engineering review but must match selected material.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>SDS</td><td>Material safety handling information and supplier source</td><td>SDS is not a performance certificate; it supports safety and handling review.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>ISO 9001</td><td>Factory quality management certificate if available</td><td>Factory system certificates should be checked for company name, validity, and scope.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>IP Rating Notes</h2>\n<p>A gasket alone should not be described as IP65 or IP66 certified. IP-rated sealing belongs to the final enclosure assembly and test condition. We can help choose materials and processes commonly used for IP-rated enclosure sealing support.</p>\n<h2>Preferred Compliance Wording</h2>\n<p>SealBridge Supply helps coordinate material documents and compliance information such as RoHS, REACH, UL94 material grade information, TDS, and SDS when available from production partners. Final suitability should be confirmed based on the selected material, supplier document, and project application.</p>','Quality &amp; Compliance','','inherit','closed','closed','','9-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:48:15','2026-07-09 17:48:15','',9,'http://localhost:8080/?p=87',0,'revision','',0),(88,0,'2026-07-10 01:48:15','2026-07-09 17:48:15','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply is a sourcing and project coordination partner focused on custom gaskets for electrical enclosures, control cabinets, and outdoor equipment.</p></div>\n<h2>Company Background</h2>\n<p>SealBridge Supply was created for overseas B2B buyers who need custom rubber, silicone, and foam gasket support but do not want to spend weeks sorting out materials, processes, supplier communication, samples, and compliance documents. The brand focuses on electrical enclosure, control cabinet, junction box, EV charger cabinet, solar inverter enclosure, LED lighting housing, telecom cabinet, and HVAC equipment sealing projects.</p>\n<p>We position ourselves as a custom gasket sourcing and project coordination partner. That means we do not present every product as if it comes from one single factory. Instead, we help customers clarify the project requirement, match the suitable process route, coordinate samples and supplier information, and organize quotation details before production follow-up.</p>\n<h2>What We Coordinate</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Material comparison for EPDM, silicone, NBR, CR, EVA, PU foam, and other gasket materials</li><li>Process matching for die cutting, compression molding, rubber extrusion, adhesive backing, and custom sampling</li><li>Supplier communication, sample photos, product videos, packaging details, and quote parameters</li><li>Document support such as TDS, SDS, RoHS, REACH, and UL94 material information when available</li></ul>\n<h2>Supplier Network</h2>\n<p>We maintain a working network of 20+ screened production partners and factory contacts across rubber, silicone, foam, adhesive-backed die cutting, molding, and extrusion directions. The number is used as a practical sourcing range rather than a claim that every project will use every factory. For each inquiry, we select partners based on product fit, process route, sample response, document support, and communication quality.</p>\n<h2>Who We Serve</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Electrical enclosure manufacturers</li><li>Control cabinet manufacturers</li><li>Junction box manufacturers</li><li>EV charger cabinet manufacturers</li><li>Solar inverter enclosure manufacturers</li><li>LED lighting housing manufacturers</li></ul>\n<h2>How We Work</h2>\n<p>Our work starts from application and drawing review, not from a generic price list. A useful gasket quote usually needs the drawing, material target, thickness or profile size, hardness or density, adhesive requirement, quantity, application environment, and document requirements. We help organize those details so the supplier conversation is faster and more accurate.</p>','About','','inherit','closed','closed','','10-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:48:15','2026-07-09 17:48:15','',10,'http://localhost:8080/?p=88',0,'revision','',0),(89,1,'2026-07-10 01:48:15','2026-07-09 17:48:15','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply works with a focused network of screened production partners and factory contacts for custom rubber, silicone, foam, and adhesive-backed gasket projects.</p></div>\n<h2>Network Snapshot</h2>\n<div class=\"trust-strip\"><div><strong>20+</strong><span>screened production partners and factory contacts</span></div><div><strong>4</strong><span>core process routes covered</span></div><div><strong>5</strong><span>common compliance document types coordinated</span></div></div>\n<p>The network number is a practical sourcing range, not a promise that every supplier is used for every project. For each inquiry, we match the project to suitable partners based on product type, material, process, order quantity, sample requirement, and document needs.</p>\n<h2>Factory Screening in Practice</h2>\n<figure class=\"content-figure\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/trust/factory-screening.png\" alt=\"Factory screening and sample review template\"><figcaption>Illustrative screening scene. Real supplier names, customer files, and restricted factory photos are shared only when permitted during project communication.</figcaption></figure>\n<p>Factory screening is not only a quick name list. We compare whether the factory direction matches the product, whether the process can support the requested material and tolerance, whether the sample response is useful, and whether the supplier can support the document level required by the buyer.</p>\n<h2>Partner Factory Directions</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Factory Direction</th><th>Typical Products</th><th>Process Fit</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Die-cut gasket suppliers</td><td>Flat foam gaskets, adhesive-backed pads, rubber sheet gaskets</td><td>Die cutting, adhesive lamination, kiss cutting, sheet processing</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Rubber molding suppliers</td><td>Custom rubber gaskets, silicone parts, shaped seals</td><td>Compression molding, tooling, custom rubber compound review</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Rubber extrusion suppliers</td><td>Cabinet door strips, D-shape/P-shape seals, U-channel profiles</td><td>Profile extrusion, cutting, corner joining, long strip packing</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Foam material suppliers</td><td>EPDM foam, silicone foam, EVA, PU foam samples</td><td>Material sheet supply, density options, thickness range</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Adhesive and lamination partners</td><td>3M-backed or general adhesive-backed gasket parts</td><td>Adhesive selection, release liner, surface treatment support</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Factory Screening Conditions</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Product fit for enclosure, cabinet, foam, silicone, or adhesive-backed gasket projects</li><li>Clear process capability: die cutting, molding, extrusion, lamination, or sampling</li><li>Ability to provide real product photos, sample photos, profile details, or workshop information</li><li>Reasonable response speed for drawings, material questions, MOQ, tooling, and lead time</li><li>Document support such as TDS, SDS, RoHS, REACH, UL94 information, or ISO system certificates when available</li><li>Willingness to protect customer drawings, logos, packaging information, and confidential project files</li></ul>\n<h2>Partial Factory Workshop Display</h2>\n<div class=\"workshop-grid\"><figure><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/trust/workshop-glimpse.png\" alt=\"Clean gasket workshop display illustration\"><figcaption>Workshop capability reference for gasket sampling, material preparation, and production follow-up.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/trust/factory-screening.png\" alt=\"Supplier sample review illustration\"><figcaption>Sample, drawing, process, and supplier response are reviewed together before a factory direction is recommended.</figcaption></figure></div>\n<h2>Certificate and Document Conditions</h2>\n<p>We prefer production partners that can provide material-related documents or factory system documents when requested. However, document availability depends on the selected material, supplier, order quantity, and project requirement.</p>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Document Type</th><th>What It Supports</th><th>How It Should Be Used</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>RoHS</td><td>Restricted substance review for selected material</td><td>Check material, test date, and supplier source before quoting as supported.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>REACH</td><td>EU chemical substance requirement review</td><td>Confirm current customer requirement and document scope.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>UL94</td><td>Flammability grade information for material</td><td>Confirm material grade, thickness condition, and whether the data applies to the selected gasket.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>TDS</td><td>Technical properties such as hardness, density, tensile strength, and temperature range</td><td>Use for engineering review and material comparison.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>SDS</td><td>Safety and handling information</td><td>Use for material handling and compliance file support, not as a performance certificate.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>ISO 9001</td><td>Factory quality management system</td><td>Check company name, certificate validity, certification body, and scope.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>What We Do Not Overclaim</h2>\n<p>We do not describe every supplier as certified for every product. We do not claim that a gasket alone has IP65 or IP66 certification. We do not publish customer-specific certificates, drawings, logos, or packaging photos without permission. For formal customer projects, certificate files and supplier documents should be confirmed against the selected material and purchase requirement.</p>','Supplier Network','','trash','closed','closed','','supplier-network__trashed','','','2026-07-10 07:15:04','2026-07-09 23:15:04','',0,'http://localhost:8080/supplier-network/',0,'page','',0),(90,0,'2026-07-10 01:48:15','2026-07-09 