0 01:52:11','2026-07-09 17:52:11','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply works with a focused network of screened production partners and factory contacts for custom rubber, silicone, foam, and adhesive-backed gasket projects.</p></div>\n<h2>Network Snapshot</h2>\n<div class=\"trust-strip\"><div><strong>20+</strong><span>screened production partners and factory contacts</span></div><div><strong>4</strong><span>core process routes covered</span></div><div><strong>5</strong><span>common compliance document types coordinated</span></div></div>\n<p>The network number is a practical sourcing range, not a promise that every supplier is used for every project. For each inquiry, we match the project to suitable partners based on product type, material, process, order quantity, sample requirement, and document needs.</p>\n<h2>Partner Factory Directions</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Factory Direction</th><th>Typical Products</th><th>Process Fit</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Die-cut gasket suppliers</td><td>Flat foam gaskets, adhesive-backed pads, rubber sheet gaskets</td><td>Die cutting, adhesive lamination, kiss cutting, sheet processing</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Rubber molding suppliers</td><td>Custom rubber gaskets, silicone parts, shaped seals</td><td>Compression molding, tooling, custom rubber compound review</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Rubber extrusion suppliers</td><td>Cabinet door strips, D-shape/P-shape seals, U-channel profiles</td><td>Profile extrusion, cutting, corner joining, long strip packing</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Foam material suppliers</td><td>EPDM foam, silicone foam, EVA, PU foam samples</td><td>Material sheet supply, density options, thickness range</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Adhesive and lamination partners</td><td>3M-backed or general adhesive-backed gasket parts</td><td>Adhesive selection, release liner, surface treatment support</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Factory Screening Conditions</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Product fit for enclosure, cabinet, foam, silicone, or adhesive-backed gasket projects</li><li>Clear process capability: die cutting, molding, extrusion, lamination, or sampling</li><li>Ability to provide real product photos, sample photos, profile details, or workshop information</li><li>Reasonable response speed for drawings, material questions, MOQ, tooling, and lead time</li><li>Document support such as TDS, SDS, RoHS, REACH, UL94 information, or ISO system certificates when available</li><li>Willingness to protect customer drawings, logos, packaging information, and confidential project files</li></ul>\n<h2>Certificate and Document Conditions</h2>\n<p>We prefer production partners that can provide material-related documents or factory system documents when requested. However, document availability depends on the selected material, supplier, order quantity, and project requirement.</p>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Document Type</th><th>What It Supports</th><th>How It Should Be Used</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>RoHS</td><td>Restricted substance review for selected material</td><td>Check material, test date, and supplier source before quoting as supported.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>REACH</td><td>EU chemical substance requirement review</td><td>Confirm current customer requirement and document scope.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>UL94</td><td>Flammability grade information for material</td><td>Confirm material grade, thickness condition, and whether the data applies to the selected gasket.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>TDS</td><td>Technical properties such as hardness, density, tensile strength, and temperature range</td><td>Use for engineering review and material comparison.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>SDS</td><td>Safety and handling information</td><td>Use for material handling and compliance file support, not as a performance certificate.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>ISO 9001</td><td>Factory quality management system</td><td>Check company name, certificate validity, certification body, and scope.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>What We Do Not Overclaim</h2>\n<p>We do not describe every supplier as certified for every product. We do not claim that a gasket alone has IP65 or IP66 certification. We do not publish customer-specific certificates, drawings, logos, or packaging photos without permission. For formal customer projects, certificate files and supplier documents should be confirmed against the selected material and purchase requirement.</p>','Supplier Network','','inherit','closed','closed','','89-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 01:52:11','2026-07-09 17:52:11','',89,'http://localhost:8080/?p=101',0,'revision','',0),(102,1,'2026-07-10 01:52:11','2026-07-09 17:52:11','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Real customer certificates, supplier documents, factory photos, and test reports are not displayed publicly by default. Instead, this page shows the document fields and review logic customers can expect during a project.</p></div>\n<h2>Why We Use Templates Instead of Public Certificate Photos</h2>\n<p>Many material reports and factory certificates include supplier names, report numbers, customer projects, material codes, testing labs, and commercial information. Publishing unverified or third-party documents publicly can mislead buyers and may violate supplier or customer confidentiality. For serious inquiries, document files should be shared and checked in the project communication stage.</p>\n<h2>Certificate Review Template</h2>\n<figure class=\"content-figure\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/trust/certificate-review.png\" alt=\"Certificate review template illustration\"><figcaption>Illustrative certificate review template. It is not a real certificate photo and should be used to explain the checking method only.</figcaption></figure>\n<h2>Certificate File Checklist</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>What Should Be Confirmed</th><th>Why It Matters</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Document Type</td><td>RoHS, REACH, UL94, TDS, SDS, ISO 9001, or other document</td><td>Different documents prove different things.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Material Name / Grade</td><td>EPDM foam, silicone rubber, NBR, CR, EVA, PU foam, adhesive tape, or compound grade</td><td>The document should match the selected material.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Supplier / Factory Name</td><td>Company name, manufacturer, or material supplier shown on the document</td><td>Confirms the source and avoids using unrelated files.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Report Date / Validity</td><td>Issue date, validity period, version, or latest declaration date</td><td>Old documents may not satisfy current customer requirements.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Test Scope</td><td>Tested substances, material thickness, flammability grade, or technical properties</td><td>The scope should match the customer question.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>File Status</td><td>Available, pending supplier confirmation, sample-only, or not available</td><td>Keeps quotation communication honest and traceable.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Sample Document Status Table</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Document</th><th>Status Template</th><th>Notes to Customer</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>RoHS</td><td>Available after material confirmation</td><td>Material and supplier source must match the quoted part.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>REACH</td><td>Available / declaration pending</td><td>Confirm customer requires declaration or third-party test report.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>UL94</td><td>Material grade information available when applicable</td><td>Finished gasket is not automatically UL certified.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>TDS</td><td>Available for selected material grade</td><td>Useful for hardness, density, temperature range, and compression review.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>SDS</td><td>Available for material handling review</td><td>SDS supports safety information, not sealing performance.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>ISO 9001</td><td>Supplier-dependent</td><td>Check factory name, certification body, validity, and business scope.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>How We Share Documents During Cooperation</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Confirm the selected material and supplier before requesting files</li><li>Mark document status as available, pending, or not applicable</li><li>Check whether the file scope matches the buyer requirement</li><li>Share documents privately in project communication when permitted</li><li>Avoid publishing customer-specific reports or supplier files publicly</li><li>Keep a project document checklist for repeat orders and future inquiries</li></ul>','Certificate Templates','','trash','closed','closed','','certificate-templates__trashed','','','2026-07-10 07:15:04','2026-07-09 23:15:04','',0,'http://localhost:8080/certificate-templates/',0,'page','',0),(103,1,'2026-07-10 01:52:11','2026-07-09 17:52:11','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply is built around follow-up service: clarifying requirements, organizing supplier communication, preparing document checklists, and keeping project information reusable for future cooperation.</p></div>\n<h2>Our Service Advantages</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Focused category knowledge around enclosure gaskets, cabinet seals, foam gaskets, silicone gaskets, and adhesive-backed die-cut parts</li><li>Bilingual sourcing coordination between overseas buyers and Chinese production partners</li><li>Supplier matching based on material, process, sample feasibility, document support, and order quantity</li><li>Clear quote checklists that reduce repeated communication and wrong assumptions</li><li>Document-first mindset for RoHS, REACH, UL94, TDS, SDS, and supplier certificates when available</li><li>Project files that can be reused for repeat orders, product page updates, and future sourcing</li></ul>\n<h2>How We Serve a New Inquiry</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Stage</th><th>What We Do</th><th>Customer Output</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>1. Requirement intake</td><td>Review drawing, photo, application, material target, quantity, and compliance needs</td><td>Clean quote checklist</td></tr>\n<tr><td>2. Material direction</td><td>Compare EPDM, silicone, NBR, CR, EVA, PU foam, adhesive backing, and process route</td><td>Suggested material/process direction</td></tr>\n<tr><td>3. Supplier matching</td><td>Select suitable screened production partners or factory contacts</td><td>Supplier quote request package</td></tr>\n<tr><td>4. Quote coordination</td><td>Clarify MOQ, tooling, lead time, sample cost, document support, and packaging details</td><td>More complete quotation information</td></tr>\n<tr><td>5. Sample follow-up</td><td>Coordinate sample photos, sample labels, shipment details, and feedback collection</td><td>Sample review file</td></tr>\n<tr><td>6. Repeat cooperation</td><td>Keep material, drawing, supplier, quote, and document notes for future orders</td><td>Reusable project record</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Follow-up File Structure</h2>\n<p>For ongoing cooperation, we can organize each project around a simple file structure:</p>\n<ul><li>Product name and application scenario</li><li>Drawing version and sample photos</li><li>Material, hardness or density, thickness, adhesive, and process notes</li><li>Supplier quote parameters, MOQ, tooling, and lead time</li><li>Certificate/document status: RoHS, REACH, UL94, TDS, SDS, ISO 9001 if available</li><li>Sample feedback, packaging notes, and repeat order reference</li></ul>\n<h2>How This Helps Long-term Cooperation</h2>\n<p>Many gasket projects are not one-time decisions. A buyer may start with one enclosure gasket, then add cabinet strips, foam pads, adhesive-backed parts, or another application. A reusable project record helps reduce repeated explanation, speeds up new quotations, and keeps material and document history clearer.</p>','Service &amp; Follow-up','','publish','closed','closed','','service-follow-up','','','2026-07-11 01:07:35','2026-07-10 17:07:35','',0,'http://localhost:8080/service-follow-up/',0,'page','',0),(112,0,'2026-07-10 02:03:24','2026-07-09 18:03:24','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>SealBridge Supply works with a focused network of screened production partners and factory contacts for custom rubber, silicone, foam, and adhesive-backed gasket projects.</p></div>\n<h2>Network Snapshot</h2>\n<div class=\"trust-strip\"><div><strong>20+</strong><span>screened production partners and factory contacts</span></div><div><strong>4</strong><span>core process routes covered</span></div><div><strong>5</strong><span>common compliance document types coordinated</span></div></div>\n<p>The network number is a practical sourcing range, not a promise that every supplier is used for every project. For each inquiry, we match the project to suitable partners based on product type, material, process, order quantity, sample requirement, and document needs.</p>\n<h2>Factory Screening in Practice</h2>\n<figure class=\"content-figure\"><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/trust/factory-screening.png\" alt=\"Factory screening and sample review template\"><figcaption>Illustrative screening scene. Real supplier names, customer files, and restricted factory photos are shared only when permitted during project communication.</figcaption></figure>\n<p>Factory screening is not only a quick name list. We compare whether the factory direction matches the product, whether the process can support the requested material and tolerance, whether the sample response is useful, and whether the supplier can support the document level required by the buyer.</p>\n<h2>Partner Factory Directions</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Factory Direction</th><th>Typical Products</th><th>Process Fit</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>Die-cut gasket suppliers</td><td>Flat foam gaskets, adhesive-backed pads, rubber sheet gaskets</td><td>Die cutting, adhesive lamination, kiss cutting, sheet processing</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Rubber molding suppliers</td><td>Custom rubber gaskets, silicone parts, shaped seals</td><td>Compression molding, tooling, custom rubber compound review</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Rubber extrusion suppliers</td><td>Cabinet door strips, D-shape/P-shape seals, U-channel profiles</td><td>Profile extrusion, cutting, corner joining, long strip packing</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Foam material suppliers</td><td>EPDM foam, silicone foam, EVA, PU foam samples</td><td>Material sheet supply, density options, thickness range</td></tr>\n<tr><td>Adhesive and lamination partners</td><td>3M-backed or general adhesive-backed gasket parts</td><td>Adhesive selection, release liner, surface treatment support</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Factory Screening Conditions</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Product fit for enclosure, cabinet, foam, silicone, or adhesive-backed gasket projects</li><li>Clear process capability: die cutting, molding, extrusion, lamination, or sampling</li><li>Ability to provide real product photos, sample photos, profile details, or workshop information</li><li>Reasonable response speed for drawings, material questions, MOQ, tooling, and lead time</li><li>Document support such as TDS, SDS, RoHS, REACH, UL94 information, or ISO system certificates when available</li><li>Willingness to protect customer drawings, logos, packaging information, and confidential project files</li></ul>\n<h2>Partial Factory Workshop Display</h2>\n<div class=\"workshop-grid\"><figure><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/trust/workshop-glimpse.png\" alt=\"Clean gasket workshop display illustration\"><figcaption>Workshop capability reference for gasket sampling, material preparation, and production follow-up.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src=\"/wp-content/themes/sealbridge/assets/trust/factory-screening.png\" alt=\"Supplier sample review illustration\"><figcaption>Sample, drawing, process, and supplier response are reviewed together before a factory direction is recommended.</figcaption></figure></div>\n<h2>Certificate and Document Conditions</h2>\n<p>We prefer production partners that can provide material-related documents or factory system documents when requested. However, document availability depends on the selected material, supplier, order quantity, and project requirement.</p>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Document Type</th><th>What It Supports</th><th>How It Should Be Used</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>RoHS</td><td>Restricted substance review for selected material</td><td>Check material, test date, and supplier source before quoting as supported.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>REACH</td><td>EU chemical substance requirement review</td><td>Confirm current customer requirement and document scope.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>UL94</td><td>Flammability grade information for material</td><td>Confirm material grade, thickness condition, and whether the data applies to the selected gasket.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>TDS</td><td>Technical properties such as hardness, density, tensile strength, and temperature range</td><td>Use for engineering review and material comparison.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>SDS</td><td>Safety and handling information</td><td>Use for material handling and compliance file support, not as a performance certificate.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>ISO 9001</td><td>Factory quality management system</td><td>Check company name, certificate validity, certification body, and scope.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>What We Do Not Overclaim</h2>\n<p>We do not describe every supplier as certified for every product. We do not claim that a gasket alone has IP65 or IP66 certification. We do not publish customer-specific certificates, drawings, logos, or packaging photos without permission. For formal customer projects, certificate files and supplier documents should be confirmed against the selected material and purchase requirement.</p>','Supplier Network','','inherit','closed','closed','','89-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 02:03:24','2026-07-09 18:03:24','',89,'http://localhost:8080/?p=112',0,'revision','',0),(113,0,'2026-07-10 02:03:24','2026-07-09 18:03:24','<div class=\"intro-band\"><p>Real customer certificates, supplier documents, factory photos, a