h the customer question.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>File Status</td><td>Available, pending supplier confirmation, sample-only, or not available</td><td>Keeps quotation communication honest and traceable.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Sample Document Status Table</h2>\n<table><thead><tr><th>Document</th><th>Status Template</th><th>Notes to Customer</th></tr></thead><tbody>\n<tr><td>RoHS</td><td>Available after material confirmation</td><td>Material and supplier source must match the quoted part.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>REACH</td><td>Available / declaration pending</td><td>Confirm customer requires declaration or third-party test report.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>UL94</td><td>Material grade information available when applicable</td><td>Finished gasket is not automatically UL certified.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>TDS</td><td>Available for selected material grade</td><td>Useful for hardness, density, temperature range, and compression review.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>SDS</td><td>Available for material handling review</td><td>SDS supports safety information, not sealing performance.</td></tr>\n<tr><td>ISO 9001</td><td>Supplier-dependent</td><td>Check factory name, certification body, validity, and business scope.</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>How We Share Documents During Cooperation</h2>\n<ul class=\"feature-list\"><li>Confirm the selected material and supplier before requesting files</li><li>Mark document status as available, pending, or not applicable</li><li>Check whether the file scope matches the buyer requirement</li><li>Share documents privately in project communication when permitted</li><li>Avoid publishing customer-specific reports or supplier files publicly</li><li>Keep a project document checklist for repeat orders and future inquiries</li></ul>','Certificate Templates','','inherit','closed','closed','','102-revision-v1','','','2026-07-10 02:03:24','2026-07-09 18:03:24','',102,'http://localhost:8080/?p=113',0,'revision','',0),(114,0,'2026-07-10 02:03:24','2026-07-09 18:03:24','<div cla